<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="346" pageId="4" pageNumber="345" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1734,2013]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1437,151,429]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="346" pageId="4" pageNumber="345">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1734,1760]" pageId="4" pageNumber="345">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The venter of body black, except the mesosternum mediolaterally with a yellowish-brown mark on each side directed anteriorly and posteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[594,691,1771,1797]" captionStart="FIGURES 2" captionStartId="7.[151,275,1823,1849]" captionTargetBox="[219,1372,169,1783]" captionTargetId="figure-17@7.[216,1372,164,1799]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 2. Metrocoris issaci sp. nov., apterous form: A, male, dorsal view; B, female, dorsal view; C, male, ventral view; D, male, lateral view; E, male, abdominal tip, dorsal view; F, male, abdominal tip, ventral view; G, male, abdomen, lateral view; H, female, abdomen, ventral view; I, female, abdominal tip showing coxa and trochanter of hind leg, dorsal view; J, male, abdomen, dorsal view; K, male, genital capsule, lateral view; L, male, proctiger, dorsal view; M, male, pygophore, dorsal view; N, male, paramere, lateral view; O, male, endosoma, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5792717" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5792717/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="345">Figs. 2C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[701,736,1771,1797]" captionStart="FIGURES 3" captionStartId="9.[151,275,1828,1854]" captionTargetBox="[223,1362,186,1799]" captionTargetId="figure-17@9.[219,1368,179,1805]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 3. Metrocoris josephi sp. nov.: A, macropterous male, dorsal view; B, same, ventral view; C, apterous female, dorsal view; D, apterous female, lateral view; E, macropterous membrane broken male (mac-da), lateral view; F, mac-da male, abdomen, dorsal view; G, mac-da male, abdominal tip, ventral view; H, same, lateral view; I, apterous female, abdomen, ventral view; J, apterous female, abdominal tip showing coxa and trochanter of hind leg, dorsal view; K, mac-da male, genital capsule, lateral view; L, mac-da male, proctiger, dorsal view; M, mac-da male, pygophore, dorsal view; N, mac-da male, paramere, lateral view; O, mac-da male, endosoma, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5792725" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5792725/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="345">3B</figureCitation>
), the posterior region of the abdominal venter yellowish-brown (
<figureCitation box="[159,321,1807,1833]" captionStart="FIGURES 2" captionStartId="7.[151,275,1823,1849]" captionTargetBox="[219,1372,169,1783]" captionTargetId="figure-17@7.[216,1372,164,1799]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 2. Metrocoris issaci sp. nov., apterous form: A, male, dorsal view; B, female, dorsal view; C, male, ventral view; D, male, lateral view; E, male, abdominal tip, dorsal view; F, male, abdominal tip, ventral view; G, male, abdomen, lateral view; H, female, abdomen, ventral view; I, female, abdominal tip showing coxa and trochanter of hind leg, dorsal view; J, male, abdomen, dorsal view; K, male, genital capsule, lateral view; L, male, proctiger, dorsal view; M, male, pygophore, dorsal view; N, male, paramere, lateral view; O, male, endosoma, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5792717" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5792717/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="345">Figs. 2C, F, H</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[333,425,1807,1833]" captionStart="FIGURES 3" captionStartId="9.[151,275,1828,1854]" captionTargetBox="[223,1362,186,1799]" captionTargetId="figure-17@9.[219,1368,179,1805]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 3. Metrocoris josephi sp. nov.: A, macropterous male, dorsal view; B, same, ventral view; C, apterous female, dorsal view; D, apterous female, lateral view; E, macropterous membrane broken male (mac-da), lateral view; F, mac-da male, abdomen, dorsal view; G, mac-da male, abdominal tip, ventral view; H, same, lateral view; I, apterous female, abdomen, ventral view; J, apterous female, abdominal tip showing coxa and trochanter of hind leg, dorsal view; K, mac-da male, genital capsule, lateral view; L, mac-da male, proctiger, dorsal view; M, mac-da male, pygophore, dorsal view; N, mac-da male, paramere, lateral view; O, mac-da male, endosoma, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5792725" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5792725/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="345">3B, G, I</figureCitation>
); the male fore femur is slender, the flexor region almost medially with a small notch and mostly with a few setae basally (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Tran, A. D. &amp; Polhemus, D. A." box="[568,853,1843,1869]" pageId="4" pageNumber="345" pagination="109 - 149" refId="ref11952" refString="Tran, A. D. &amp; Polhemus, D. A. (2017) The genus Metrocoris Mayr, 1865 (Gerromorpha: Gerridae) in Vietnam, with descriptions of five new species. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 65, 109 - 149." type="journal article" year="2017">Tran and Polhemus 2017</bibRefCitation>
, Fig. 100); the hind coxa or both the hind coxa and the hind trochanter with a slender process or the hind trochanter is slightly produced in female (
<figureCitation box="[1234,1357,1879,1905]" captionStart="FIGURES 2" captionStartId="7.[151,275,1823,1849]" captionTargetBox="[219,1372,169,1783]" captionTargetId="figure-17@7.[216,1372,164,1799]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 2. Metrocoris issaci sp. nov., apterous form: A, male, dorsal view; B, female, dorsal view; C, male, ventral view; D, male, lateral view; E, male, abdominal tip, dorsal view; F, male, abdominal tip, ventral view; G, male, abdomen, lateral view; H, female, abdomen, ventral view; I, female, abdominal tip showing coxa and trochanter of hind leg, dorsal view; J, male, abdomen, dorsal view; K, male, genital capsule, lateral view; L, male, proctiger, dorsal view; M, male, pygophore, dorsal view; N, male, paramere, lateral view; O, male, endosoma, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5792717" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5792717/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="345">Figs. 2B, I</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1370,1431,1879,1905]" captionStart="FIGURES 3" captionStartId="9.[151,275,1828,1854]" captionTargetBox="[223,1362,186,1799]" captionTargetId="figure-17@9.[219,1368,179,1805]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 3. Metrocoris josephi sp. nov.: A, macropterous male, dorsal view; B, same, ventral view; C, apterous female, dorsal view; D, apterous female, lateral view; E, macropterous membrane broken male (mac-da), lateral view; F, mac-da male, abdomen, dorsal view; G, mac-da male, abdominal tip, ventral view; H, same, lateral view; I, apterous female, abdomen, ventral view; J, apterous female, abdominal tip showing coxa and trochanter of hind leg, dorsal view; K, mac-da male, genital capsule, lateral view; L, mac-da male, proctiger, dorsal view; M, mac-da male, pygophore, dorsal view; N, mac-da male, paramere, lateral view; O, mac-da male, endosoma, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5792725" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5792725/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="345">3C, J</figureCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Chen, P. P. &amp; Nieser, N." box="[151,387,1915,1941]" pageId="4" pageNumber="345" pagination="1 - 43" refId="ref11660" refString="Chen, P. P. &amp; Nieser, N. (1993 a &amp; b) A taxonomic revision of the Oriental water strider genus Metrocoris Mayr (Hemiptera, Gerridae). Part I &amp; II. Steenstrupia, 19 (1 &amp; 2), 1 - 43 &amp; 45 - 82." type="journal article" year="1993">Chen &amp; Nieser 1993</bibRefCitation>
b, Fig. 204; 
<bibRefCitation author="Tran, A. D. &amp; Polhemus, D. A." box="[524,791,1915,1941]" pageId="4" pageNumber="345" pagination="109 - 149" refId="ref11952" refString="Tran, A. D. &amp; Polhemus, D. A. (2017) The genus Metrocoris Mayr, 1865 (Gerromorpha: Gerridae) in Vietnam, with descriptions of five new species. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 65, 109 - 149." type="journal article" year="2017">Tran &amp; Polhemus 2017</bibRefCitation>
, Fig. 106), the flexor region of the hind femur basally or sub-basally usually with a fringe of setae in the female (
<figureCitation box="[770,858,1951,1977]" captionStart="FIGURES 2" captionStartId="7.[151,275,1823,1849]" captionTargetBox="[219,1372,169,1783]" captionTargetId="figure-17@7.[216,1372,164,1799]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 2. Metrocoris issaci sp. nov., apterous form: A, male, dorsal view; B, female, dorsal view; C, male, ventral view; D, male, lateral view; E, male, abdominal tip, dorsal view; F, male, abdominal tip, ventral view; G, male, abdomen, lateral view; H, female, abdomen, ventral view; I, female, abdominal tip showing coxa and trochanter of hind leg, dorsal view; J, male, abdomen, dorsal view; K, male, genital capsule, lateral view; L, male, proctiger, dorsal view; M, male, pygophore, dorsal view; N, male, paramere, lateral view; O, male, endosoma, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5792717" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5792717/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="345">Figs. 2I</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[869,896,1951,1977]" captionStart="FIGURES 3" captionStartId="9.[151,275,1828,1854]" captionTargetBox="[223,1362,186,1799]" captionTargetId="figure-17@9.[219,1368,179,1805]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 3. Metrocoris josephi sp. nov.: A, macropterous male, dorsal view; B, same, ventral view; C, apterous female, dorsal view; D, apterous female, lateral view; E, macropterous membrane broken male (mac-da), lateral view; F, mac-da male, abdomen, dorsal view; G, mac-da male, abdominal tip, ventral view; H, same, lateral view; I, apterous female, abdomen, ventral view; J, apterous female, abdominal tip showing coxa and trochanter of hind leg, dorsal view; K, mac-da male, genital capsule, lateral view; L, mac-da male, proctiger, dorsal view; M, mac-da male, pygophore, dorsal view; N, mac-da male, paramere, lateral view; O, mac-da male, endosoma, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5792725" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5792725/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="345">3J</figureCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Tran, A. D. &amp; Polhemus, D. A." box="[907,1169,1951,1977]" pageId="4" pageNumber="345" pagination="109 - 149" refId="ref11952" refString="Tran, A. D. &amp; Polhemus, D. A. (2017) The genus Metrocoris Mayr, 1865 (Gerromorpha: Gerridae) in Vietnam, with descriptions of five new species. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 65, 109 - 149." type="journal article" year="2017">Tran &amp; Polhemus 2017</bibRefCitation>
, Fig. 106); the proctiger of the male is sub-ovate, mediolaterally widened (
<figureCitation box="[711,808,1987,2013]" captionStart="FIGURES 2" captionStartId="7.[151,275,1823,1849]" captionTargetBox="[219,1372,169,1783]" captionTargetId="figure-17@7.[216,1372,164,1799]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 2. Metrocoris issaci sp. nov., apterous form: A, male, dorsal view; B, female, dorsal view; C, male, ventral view; D, male, lateral view; E, male, abdominal tip, dorsal view; F, male, abdominal tip, ventral view; G, male, abdomen, lateral view; H, female, abdomen, ventral view; I, female, abdominal tip showing coxa and trochanter of hind leg, dorsal view; J, male, abdomen, dorsal view; K, male, genital capsule, lateral view; L, male, proctiger, dorsal view; M, male, pygophore, dorsal view; N, male, paramere, lateral view; O, male, endosoma, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5792717" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5792717/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="345">Figs. 2L</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[820,854,1987,2013]" captionStart="FIGURES 3" captionStartId="9.[151,275,1828,1854]" captionTargetBox="[223,1362,186,1799]" captionTargetId="figure-17@9.[219,1368,179,1805]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 3. Metrocoris josephi sp. nov.: A, macropterous male, dorsal view; B, same, ventral view; C, apterous female, dorsal view; D, apterous female, lateral view; E, macropterous membrane broken male (mac-da), lateral view; F, mac-da male, abdomen, dorsal view; G, mac-da male, abdominal tip, ventral view; H, same, lateral view; I, apterous female, abdomen, ventral view; J, apterous female, abdominal tip showing coxa and trochanter of hind leg, dorsal view; K, mac-da male, genital capsule, lateral view; L, mac-da male, proctiger, dorsal view; M, mac-da male, pygophore, dorsal view; N, mac-da male, paramere, lateral view; O, mac-da male, endosoma, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5792725" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5792725/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="345">3L</figureCitation>
); the paramere is falciform, the dorsal region nearly middle is slightly raised usually with some setae (
<figureCitation box="[731,833,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURES 2" captionStartId="7.[151,275,1823,1849]" captionTargetBox="[219,1372,169,1783]" captionTargetId="figure-17@7.[216,1372,164,1799]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 2. Metrocoris issaci sp. nov., apterous form: A, male, dorsal view; B, female, dorsal view; C, male, ventral view; D, male, lateral view; E, male, abdominal tip, dorsal view; F, male, abdominal tip, ventral view; G, male, abdomen, lateral view; H, female, abdomen, ventral view; I, female, abdominal tip showing coxa and trochanter of hind leg, dorsal view; J, male, abdomen, dorsal view; K, male, genital capsule, lateral view; L, male, proctiger, dorsal view; M, male, pygophore, dorsal view; N, male, paramere, lateral view; O, male, endosoma, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5792717" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5792717/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="346">Figs. 2N</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[848,885,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURES 3" captionStartId="9.[151,275,1828,1854]" captionTargetBox="[223,1362,186,1799]" captionTargetId="figure-17@9.[219,1368,179,1805]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 3. Metrocoris josephi sp. nov.: A, macropterous male, dorsal view; B, same, ventral view; C, apterous female, dorsal view; D, apterous female, lateral view; E, macropterous membrane broken male (mac-da), lateral view; F, mac-da male, abdomen, dorsal view; G, mac-da male, abdominal tip, ventral view; H, same, lateral view; I, apterous female, abdomen, ventral view; J, apterous female, abdominal tip showing coxa and trochanter of hind leg, dorsal view; K, mac-da male, genital capsule, lateral view; L, mac-da male, proctiger, dorsal view; M, mac-da male, pygophore, dorsal view; N, mac-da male, paramere, lateral view; O, mac-da male, endosoma, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5792725" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5792725/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="346">3N</figureCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Chen, P. P. &amp; Nieser, N." box="[900,1141,151,177]" pageId="5" pageNumber="346" pagination="1 - 43" refId="ref11660" refString="Chen, P. P. &amp; Nieser, N. (1993 a &amp; b) A taxonomic revision of the Oriental water strider genus Metrocoris Mayr (Hemiptera, Gerridae). Part I &amp; II. Steenstrupia, 19 (1 &amp; 2), 1 - 43 &amp; 45 - 82." type="journal article" year="1993">Chen &amp; Nieser 1993</bibRefCitation>
b, Figs. 193, 194; 
<bibRefCitation author="Tran, A. D. &amp; Polhemus, D. A." pageId="5" pageNumber="346" pagination="109 - 149" refId="ref11952" refString="Tran, A. D. &amp; Polhemus, D. A. (2017) The genus Metrocoris Mayr, 1865 (Gerromorpha: Gerridae) in Vietnam, with descriptions of five new species. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 65, 109 - 149." type="journal article" year="2017">Tran &amp; Polhemus 2017</bibRefCitation>
, Figs. 101, 102); the proximal region of the dorsal sclerite with a reflex angled process, the ventral sclerite of endosoma is long, surpassing well beyond the level of the lateral sclerite in the lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[1341,1432,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURES 2" captionStartId="7.[151,275,1823,1849]" captionTargetBox="[219,1372,169,1783]" captionTargetId="figure-17@7.[216,1372,164,1799]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 2. Metrocoris issaci sp. nov., apterous form: A, male, dorsal view; B, female, dorsal view; C, male, ventral view; D, male, lateral view; E, male, abdominal tip, dorsal view; F, male, abdominal tip, ventral view; G, male, abdomen, lateral view; H, female, abdomen, ventral view; I, female, abdominal tip showing coxa and trochanter of hind leg, dorsal view; J, male, abdomen, dorsal view; K, male, genital capsule, lateral view; L, male, proctiger, dorsal view; M, male, pygophore, dorsal view; N, male, paramere, lateral view; O, male, endosoma, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5792717" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5792717/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="346">Fig. 2O</figureCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Chen, P. P. &amp; Nieser, N." box="[151,390,259,285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="346" pagination="1 - 43" refId="ref11660" refString="Chen, P. P. &amp; Nieser, N. (1993 a &amp; b) A taxonomic revision of the Oriental water strider genus Metrocoris Mayr (Hemiptera, Gerridae). Part I &amp; II. Steenstrupia, 19 (1 &amp; 2), 1 - 43 &amp; 45 - 82." type="journal article" year="1993">Chen &amp; Nieser 1993</bibRefCitation>
b, Fig. 200, 
<bibRefCitation author="Tran, A. D. &amp; Polhemus, D. A." box="[529,800,259,285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="346" pagination="109 - 149" refId="ref11952" refString="Tran, A. D. &amp; Polhemus, D. A. (2017) The genus Metrocoris Mayr, 1865 (Gerromorpha: Gerridae) in Vietnam, with descriptions of five new species. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 65, 109 - 149." type="journal article" year="2017">Tran &amp; Polhemus 2017</bibRefCitation>
, Fig. 104); the sternum VII of the female is constricted laterally and is completely covering the genital segments (
